    "answer_id" : 18423505,
    "question_id" : 2254435,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>I'm no expert, but I do believe that the <code>null</code> equivalent for an int is <code>0</code>.</p>\n\n<p>For example, if you make an <code>int[]</code>, each slot contains <code>0</code> as opposed to <code>null</code>, unless you set it to something else.</p>\n\n<p>In some situations, this may be of use.</p>\n"
  }, {
