    "answer_id" : 23176253,
    "question_id" : 2254435,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Check for null in your check() method and return an invalid value such as -1 or zero if null.  Then the check would be for that value rather than passing the null along.  This would be a normal thing to do in old time 'C'.</p>\n"
