    "answer_id" : 62937116,
    "question_id" : 2254435,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>An int is not null, it may be 0 if not initialized. If you want an integer to be able to be null, you need to use Integer instead of int . primitives don't have null value. default have for an int is 0.</p>\n<p>Data Type   /  Default Value (for fields)</p>\n<p>int  ------------------       0</p>\n<p>long ----------------    0L</p>\n<p>float   ----------------    0.0f</p>\n<p>double    -------------  0.0d</p>\n<p>char     ---------------   '\\u0000'</p>\n<p>String    ---------------  null</p>\n<p>boolean  ------------   false</p>\n"
  } ],
